RSUE - Class in choiceModel
Although it is not computationally the most efficient, the RSUE is implemented as a special case of the RSUET where the threshold is infinity.

RSUET - Class in choiceModel
This class of route choice models, originated from Thomas Kjær Rasmussen of the Technical University of Denmark, has extremely attractive computational properties when the lower reference cost phi function equals RefCostMin
RSUET(RUM, RefCostFun, RefCostFun) - Constructor for class choiceModel.RSUET
Only class constructor, since the RSUET requires two reference costs in order to make sense.
rum - Variable in class choiceModel.RouteChoiceModel
 
RUM - Class in choiceModel
This abstract class means to structure the different types of random utility models that exist; note that a RUM is not a route choice model, but rather route choice models may have associated with them some RUM (even though this does not necessarily have to be the case, for instance in the case of the DUE).
